    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-08-15T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-08-15T02:00:00-05:00" n="260"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d260">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.002/472: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-15T16:00:00+09:00"
                            >August 15, 1941—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 15—8:48 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1243. An official of the Foreign Office told a member of the Embassy staff that
                        Hiranuma’s<note n="89" xml:id="d260fn89">Baron Kiichiro Hiranuma, Japanese
                        Vice Premier and Minister without Portfolio.</note> assailant was a member
                    of a “radical” organization entitled the Mitsubikai and that the motive for the
                    attack was undoubtedly resentment against Hiranuma’s efforts to bring about an
                    adjustment of Japanese-American relations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
